  "texts": [
    "The MNIST dataset 30 is a classic handwritten digit recognition dataset widely used in machine learning and computer vision research and education.",
    "It consists of a collection of samples representing digits from 0 to 9, with each sample being a grayscale image of size 28x28 pixels.",
    "The MNIST dataset contains 60,000 training samples and 10,000 testing samples.",
    "The training samples are used to train models, while the testing samples are used to evaluate model performance.",
    "These samples are handwritten by different individuals, covering various styles and variations."
  ],
